Subject: [PROPOSAL] Optimization: Move Wear Data Sync to Foreground

Reason:
Currently, `WearDataLayerService` runs as a background service triggered by `com.google.android.gms.wearable.DATA_CHANGED`.
It parses data and broadcasts it locally via `LocalBroadcastManager`.
This occurs even if the Wear app is in the background or closed, consuming battery unnecessarily (unless Complications are used, which appear to be absent).

Proposal:
Move the data listening logic directly to `MainActivity` (or a lifecycle-aware component bound to UI).
Use `Wearable.getDataClient(context).addListener(listener)` in `onResume()` and `removeListener(listener)` in `onPause()`.
This ensures data is processed only when the user is looking at the app.

--- a/wear/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml
+++ b/wear/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml
@@ -application
     ...
-    <service
-        android:name=".WearDataLayerService"
-        android:exported="true">
-        <intent-filter>
-            <action android:name="com.google.android.gms.wearable.DATA_CHANGED" />
-            <data android:scheme="wear" android:host="*" android:pathPrefix="/score" />
-            <!-- Add other paths -->
-        </intent-filter>
-    </service>
     ...

